Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js App Router

## Changes Made

1. **Installed @vercel/analytics package**
   - Added @vercel/analytics as a dependency in package.json
   - Updated package-lock.json with the new dependency and its sub-dependencies

2. **Configured Analytics in root layout**
   - Modified: src/app/layout.tsx
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the AppShell component
   - This ensures analytics are tracked across all pages of the application

## Implementation Details

The project uses the Next.js App Router (app directory), so the Analytics component was added to the root layout file (src/app/layout.tsx). The component is placed at the end of the body tag, which is the recommended location according to Vercel's documentation. This allows the Analytics script to load without blocking the main content rendering.

## Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ All routes generated properly (31 static pages)
- ✅ No TypeScript errors introduced
- ✅ Changes preserve existing code structure and functionality

## Files Modified

- package.json - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- package-lock.json - Updated with new dependency tree
- src/app/layout.tsx - Added Analytics import and component

The analytics will now track page views and web vitals automatically when the application is deployed to Vercel.
